THE GAME
--------

  'MLink' is a Workbench game based on the well known puzzle where
you try to recreate four coloured chains, one in each column.
Unlike the real game, MLink's four sides are 'flattened' on a
4 x 4 game board, but it is played just like the original game.

  You can move the top and bottom tiles horizontally (if you move
the tiles to the right, the rightmost tile will go to the left,
and vice-versa if you move the tiles to the left). The tiles can
slide up or down to where the empty space is located.

  Try to solve the puzzle in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

NOTE: The original game using arrows to move the chainlinks is no
      longer included in this archive, to get that version, please
download 'MLink_old.lha', which is also available on Aminet.

